20. The chute system as defined in claim 19, wherein the upper wall of each chute segment is generally triangular in shape and includes:
an apex proximate the post;
an outer edge proximate the outer wall;
opposed first and second side edges extending between the apex and the outer edge:
a first flange that extends outwardly and in a first direction from the first side edge; and
a second flange that extends outwardly and in a second direction from the second side edge.
